      • FOUND

        @Deprecated
public static final NanoHTTPD.Response.Status FOUND
        Deprecated. 
        Many user agents mishandle 302 in ways that violate the RFC1945 spec (i.e., redirect a POST to a GET). 303 and 307 were added in RFC2616 to address this. You should prefer 303 and 307 unless the calling user agent does not support 303 and 307 functionality
